Package:        nqrustbackup-universal-client
Architecture:   any
Pre-Depends:    debconf (>= 1.4.30) | debconf-2.0, adduser
Depends:        lsb-base (>= 3.2-13), lsof, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Provides:       nqrustbackup-universal-filedaemon (= ${binary:Version}), nqrustbackup-filedaemon (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts:      nqrustbackup-filedaemon, nqrustbackup-common
Description: Backup Archiving Recovery Open Sourced - universal client
 NQRustBackup is a set of programs to manage backup, recovery and verification of
 data across a network of computers of different kinds.
 .
 The file daemon has to be installed on the machine to be backed up. It is
 responsible for providing the file attributes and data when requested by
 the Director, and also for the file system-dependent part of restoration.
 .
 This package contains the NQRustBackup Universal Client for Linux.
